SUPPLEMENTAL NOTICE FOR AUSTRALIAN RESIDENTS
The information provided in this notice applies only to Australian residents.
This notice includes additional provisions for the purposes of our compliance with the
Privacy Act 1988
(Cth) (
Privacy Act
), including the Australian Privacy Principles (
APPs
).
This notice for Australian residents supplements and extends the scope of our Privacy Policy generally. Whatnot’s general Privacy Policy includes information about how we manage your personal information, including the kinds of personal information we collect, how we collect your personal information and the purposes for which your personal information is collected, held, used and disclosed. These policies and practices apply equally in Australia and you should consider those matters in detail in connection with this supplemental notice.
Personal information.
In this Privacy Policy, references to ‘personal information’ means information or an opinion about an identified individual, or an individual who is reasonably identifiable:
- whether the information or opinion is true or not; and
-whether the information or opinion is recorded in a material form or not.
Personal information we collect.
For the purposes of the “Personal Information We Collect” section of this Privacy Policy, User Content (as the term is defined in this Privacy Policy) is subject to this Privacy Policy.
Processing.
In this Privacy Policy, references to ‘processing’ includes the collection, holding, use and, or, disclosure of personal information, as applicable in context (and ‘process’ and ‘processed’ will be construed accordingly).
Use and disclosure.
In addition to the purposes set out above in the Privacy Policy, we may also use or disclose your personal information for any other purposes permitted by the Privacy Act.
International Data Transfers
. For the purposes of the “International Data Transfers” section of this Privacy Policy, i
f we transfer your personal information to countries outside Australia, we will ensure that the recipient is subject to enforceable law or binding scheme that is substantially similar to Australian privacy law to the APPs (as required in accordance with APP 8.2) or we will put in place appropriate mechanisms to ensure that this transfer otherwise complies with the Privacy Act, including obtaining enforceable contractual commitments from the overseas recipients to comply with the APPs.
